@node Intro   "Introduction"
@next Install
@toc  Main
AmiMDC800 1.0+                                              12-Jun-2000




     AmiMDC800  is a program to transfer images from the Mustek MDC 800
     Digital  Camera.   It  also  allows to control most of the cameras
     features. In the future it will maybe support older Mustek models.      

     Requirements: 

       Computer       : Almost any Amiga
       Camera         : Mustek MDC800
       Kickstart & WB : 3.1
       MUI            : 3.8
       Installer      : 44.10  

     This  program  ist  developed and tested under OS 3.5 and is fully
     Y2K  proof :) Following hardware was used :  Warpengine 040/40 and
     IOBlix & HyperCOM3 serial cards.

@endnode

@node Install "Installation"
@next Use_1
@toc  Main
AmiMDC800 1.0+                                              12-Jun-2000





        To  install  the  program  simply click on the install icon and
        follow all the steps.

        If  you  want to change some settings you can manually edit the
        tooltypes. The following tooltypes are supported:

		DEVICE=serial device name   (default serial.device)
                UNIT=serial device unit     (default 0)
                BAUD=serial device baudrate (default 57600)
                AUTOINIT=send init sequence (default NO)
                PUBSCREEN=screen name       (default Workbench)
                SERBUFSIZE=buffer size      (default 32768)
                SERDELAY=delay		    (default 10/50 sec)
                NOTSHARED                   (default NO) 

        At  the  moment  the software has some troubles with other baud
        rates higher than 57600 so I recommend that you don't change it.

@endnode

@node Use_1 "Usage - Page 1"
@next Use_2
@toc  Main
AmiMDC800 1.0+                                              12-Jun-2000





     After  the program is started you shoud see 3 groups, the toolbar,
     the preview area, and the status area.

     The toolbar buttons are from left to right:
	
     @{b}Exit@{ub} -------------------------------------------------------------

     Take a guess.


     @{b}Init@{ub} -------------------------------------------------------------

     Send  the initialization sequence to the camera.  If the camera is
     off  at  this  moment  you have to turn it on and send the sequece
     again.   If the AUTOINIT tooltype is set to NO or noit present you
     have to use this option manually.


     @{b}Status@{ub} -----------------------------------------------------------

     Gets  the  number  of  images  in  the  camera, the number of free
     images, and the status of some internal settings.  This command is
     also sent by AUTOINIT=YES.


     @{b}Exposure Settings@{ub} ------------------------------------------------

     Here you can set up the exposure settings and the image quality. See
     also @{" Settings Window " LINK "Use_3"}


@endnode

@node Use_2 "Usage - Page 2"
@next Use_3
@toc  Main
AmiMDC800 1.0+                                              12-Jun-2000





     @{b}Get Thumbnails@{ub} ---------------------------------------------------

     Download  all the preview thumbnail pictures from the camera.  The
     are stored as .jpg images in RAM:

     Before you use this button please use the "Status" button first if
     you don't have the tooltype AUTOINIT set to YES.


     @{b}Get Images@{ub} -------------------------------------------------------

     Download all full images from the camera.  You will be asked for a
     path where the images are stored.


     @{b}Capture Picture@{ub} --------------------------------------------------

     Sets  the  camera  to  record  mode  and  capture  a picture.  The
     thumbnail is automatically added to the preview area.
 

     @{b}View@{ub} -------------------------------------------------------------

     Not implemented yet.


     @{b}Animation@{ub} --------------------------------------------------------

     Not supported yet.

@endnode

@node Use_3 "Settings Window"
@next Context
@toc  Main
AmiMDC800 1.0+                                              12-Jun-2000





     @{b}White Balance@{ub} ----------------------------------------------------

     Set  the  white  balance  according  to  the  environmental  light
     conditions. From left to right: AUTO, INDOOR-, INDOOR+, OUTDOOR.


     @{b}Exposure Value@{ub} ---------------------------------------------------

     Set the exposure value in the range -2, -1, 0, +1 +2


     @{b}Exposure Mode@{ub} ----------------------------------------------------

     Set exposure mode to center or matrix.


     @{b}Image Quality@{ub} ----------------------------------------------------

     Set the image quality to Economic, Standard, or High


@endnode

@node Context "The contextmenu"
@next Status
@toc  Main
AmiMDC800 1.0+                                              12-Jun-2000





     If  you  click  with  the right mouse button while you are over an
     image preview a context menu will open where you can choose one of
     the followimg actions:

     Transfer   - Transfer the selected image.

     ->fxPaint  - Load the selected image into fxPaint.

     ->ImageFX  - Load the selected image into ImageFX.

     Lock       - Lock the image. It can't be deleted.

     Lock All   - Not implemented yet.

     Unlock     - Unlock the imgae. It can be deleted.

     Unlock All - Not implemented yet.

     Delete     - Delete the selected image.


@endnode

@node Status "Status Buttons"
@next History
@toc  Main
AmiMDC800 1.0+                                              12-Jun-2000





     On the right side of the window you see the camera status display.
     All  settings  can be altered by using the assigned button.  A red
     LED  means  that  the feature is on a green on that the feature is
     off.

     # T               - total images hold by the camera.
     # L               - memory left for n images (3 resolutions)

     Flash status      - Flash status ON or OFF
     Red Eye reduction - Red eye reduction active ON or OFF
     Menu display      - Camera menu display ON or OFF
     Info display      - Info display ON or OFF
     LC display        - Camera LCD ON or OFF
     Camera mode       - Camera in playback or capture mode
     NTSC Video        - Output video system PAL or NTSC
     Auto Power Off    - Auto power off aktive ON or OFF

     Camera I/O        - shows serial line activity

@endnode

